{
  "texts": [
    "Let X ⊂ R d be the d-dimensional feature space from which the samples are drawn, andY = [k] = {1, • • •, K} be the label space.",
    "Given a clean training dataset, S = {(x n, y n)} N n=1, where each (x n, y n) is drawn i.i.d.",
    "from an unknown distribution, D, over X × Y.",
    "We denote the ground-truth distribution over different labels for sample x by q(k|x), andK k=1 q(k|x) = 1.The distribution is singular: since there is only one corresponding label y for a x, we have q(y|x) = 1 and q(k ̸ = y|x) = 0.A classifier is defined as h(x) = arg max i f (x) i, where f: X → C, C ⊆ [0, 1] K is a simplex (i.e., ∀c ∈ C, 1 T c = 1), mapping feature space to label space.",
    "In this work, f is a DNN with a softmax output layer."
  ]
}